snippet.textDisplay:
My small biz is already taking a hit. So is everyone else I know, from beauty shops to motorcycle shops to restaurants.

We need real leadership in Washington now more than ever. If we do not elect leaders who are willing to substantively invest in us, the people, then this virus will grow the rich/poor gap exponentially.

Trump so far has moved to bail out the rich with our tax money - to bolster the bottom lines of oil and gas companies by announcing a massive federal purchase for the nation's Strategic Petroleum Reserve (SPR) exceeding $2.6 billion in public funds on top of the $1.5 trillion bailout for Wall Street he promised on Thursday.

Now is not the time to give up on leaders like Bernie Sanders who called for substantive measure that will protect us: Medicare for All, paid sick leave, a halt on evictions and foreclosures during this national crisis.

Remember, our taxes should work for us. Government of the people, by the people, for the people.

If you know anyone in upcoming primary states, please get them out to vote, even if it's with a mail-in ballot. Or you can make calls - check out berniesanders.com

It's time to invest in main street before it further crumbles. This is serious.
